[Verse 1]

Do you still feel my voice, a whisper above?

Does it glow warmer since you faded from view?

Did you find peace, or do shadows still stain?

Say you’re still here, just one more goodbye.

Please wake me, hold me, take me back in,
I’m slipping away, where the darkness begins.

[Verse 2]
Do you recall that November night chill,
Your kiss held me captive, time standing still?
If you could rewind, would you hold on tight,
Or leave me alone in this endless night?
I’ll love you forever, through breath and through bone,
Even in silence, even alone.
I’m sorry I faltered, I’m sorry I’m late,

[Pre-Chorus]
Looking back now, would you change what we had?
Would you rewrite our pages, erasing the bad?
I’d live it all over, each joy, every scar,
But I’m lost in this memory, you feel so far.

[Chorus]
Baby, forgive me, it’s taken this long,
The words weren’t perfect; I got them wrong.
Say this is fiction, say it’s a lie,
Say you’re still here, just one more goodbye.
But this house feels colder, our love out of reach,
I’m a ghost in our story, haunting each speech.
Please wake me, hold me, take me back in,
I’m slipping away, where the darkness begins.

Our life replays like a broken screen.

My journey isn't over, it’s only just begun,

No looking back, no ties to hold me down,

[Intro] 
And though the scars remain, they carry on, day by day 
Holding onto the fragments, finding strength along the way 
For even in the darkness, a single spark can ignite 
A love that burns forever, a beacon in the night

[Verse 1]
The screen flickers blue, another year gone by
Their words on the wall, a digital lullaby
Lonely echoes of bravado, a heart on the mend
Then Sadie's name appears, a new story begins

[Pre-Chorus]
And suddenly the colors shift, from grayscale to gold
They’re laughing in the sunlight, a story yet untold
Holding onto hope, a fragile kind of grace
In her eyes, he sees a future, a love he can embrace

[Chorus 1]
Finding Sadie in November, a flicker in the dark
The promise of forever, a love that left its mark 
But shadows still linger, a whisper in the night
Can he outrun the darkness, can he hold onto the light? 

[Instrumental Break] 

[Verse 2]
A ring on Valentine's Day, a baby on the way
They’re building a new life, trying to keep the ghosts at bay
But life's a fickle lover, a cruel and twisted game 
And the darkness whispers back, calling them by name 

[Pre-Chorus]
The laughter fades to silence, the joy begins to wane 
They fight to keep their grip, but the storm is coming, the rain
Whispers of "what if" and "why him," the guilt, the fear, the shame 
Another soul lost too soon, another love in vain 

[Chorus 2]
Finding peace in the wreckage, searching for a way to mend
The weight of the world on their shoulders, a journey with no end
She screams into the void, but the silence screams louder still 
Can love bloom in the ruins, can hope survive the kill?

[Bridge]
They visit a grave, adorned with toys and faded flowers
The ghost of a memory, a love lost in the darkest hours
"I'm sorry," she whispers, tears falling like the rain
"We’ll find you again someday, my son, no more pain."

[Verse 1]
From the basement, I excavated a deeper hole,
Lost sight of the sky, lost all self-control,
All my demons wore familiar faces,
I fought them off, but ultimately embraced their traces.

[Verse 2]
Tried to evolve, but I lost my direction,
Realized that love alone isn't always protection,
Crossed every boundary that kept me secure,
Now buried beneath the weight I could not endure.

The demons came alive when I shut my eyes,
They stole the joy, replacing it with lies,
Yet somewhere in that abyss, I found a spark,
Igniting a flame to help me navigate the dark.

[Chorus 1]
I'm constructing a new foundation, brick by shattered brick,
Confronting my inner demons, learning how to live,
Every ending’s an opportunity to start again,
So I rise from the ashes of where I’ve been.

[Verse 3]
Each dry erase board holds a brand new start,
I can't rewrite history, but I can redefine my part,
Releasing the cold, brutal love that held me,
Forgiving myself before old regrets overwhelm me.

[Verse 4]
I penned my story down for my children to see,
To understand who I was and who I'm striving to be,
Love has the power to lift or destroy,
But I refuse to let it turn me into an empty decoy.

[Pre-Chorus 2]
I’m the underdog, but I'm never down for long,
I rise from every scar, reclaim all that's gone,
Pain has transformed into strength I never knew,
My heart beats stronger, surviving every bruise.

I’m standing in the storm, but I won't fade away,
There are mountains ahead, and I’ve still got words to say,
My journey isn't over, it’s only just begun,
I’ll rise again, striving until I find the sun.

[Bridge 1]
I nearly surrendered, lost myself in the fog,
Almost crashed headfirst with nothing left to jog,
But those I love held on when I was sinking,
They saw the light that I couldn’t bring to thinking.

So now I write to inspire, I release the pain,
Turn my past into fuel, let the fire sustain,
I will not be the man who blurs the lines,
I’ll hold on to hope, and let the darkness unwind,

Laying down my hatred, rekindling desire.

[Chorus 1]
I'm constructing a new foundation, brick by shattered brick,
Confronting my inner demons, learning how to live,

So I rise from the ashes of where I’ve been.

I’m standing in the storm, but I won't fade away,
There are mountains ahead, and I’ve still got words to say,
My journey isn't over, it’s only just begun,
I’ll rise again, striving until I find the sun.

[Outro]
One step forward, feet firmly on the ground,
No looking back, no ties to hold me down,
My rearview's full of ghosts that I’ve set free,
The path is clear now, I'm ready to become me.

metadata.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
In the quiet of the morning, when the world is still asleep,
I watch the rise and fall of you, beside me in the sheets.
The fan hums a lullaby, a rhythm slow and worn,
But there’s a darkness in the silence, in the shadow before dawn.
Your hand rests on a promise, a life beneath your skin,
But something in the air tonight feels colder than it’s been.
You shift beneath the weight of dreams that you can’t leave behind,
And I can’t shake the feeling that we’re running out of time.

[Pre-Chorus]
I see the edges blur, where light and shadow meet,
A storm behind the curtains, where the heart skips its beat.
You smile, but I can’t shake this fear, that lingers in my chest,
A quiet whisper telling me we’re teetering on the edge.

[Chorus]
We’re standing on the edge where shadows blur the light,
The dawn is creeping closer, but we won’t give up the fight.
We’ll burn before the morning, but we’ll rage against the night!
With hearts still pounding, we’ll hold on to what’s right,
We’ll burn before the morning, but we’ll rage against the night!

[Verse 2]
You say you’re feeling different, like something’s not quite right,
And I brush your hair back softly, but the worry’s in your eyes.
I tell you we’ll be fine, but my words feel like a lie,
As I hold you closer, wishing time would pass us by.
The world outside is waking, but our quiet keeps me still,
I’d give anything to freeze this time, to bend it to my will.
Your laughter fills the silence, but it trembles at the seams,
And I know we’re on the edge of breaking all our dreams.

[Pre-Chorus]
I see the shadows growing, crawling through the night,
There’s something in the air that we just can’t make right.
You smile, but there’s a sadness in the way you hold my hand,
Like you know the morning's coming, with a fate we can’t withstand.

[Chorus]
We’re standing on the edge where shadows blur the light,
The dawn is creeping closer, but we won’t give up the fight.
We’ll burn before the morning, but we’ll rage against the night!
With hearts still pounding, we’ll hold on to what’s right,
We’ll burn before the morning, but we’ll rage against the night!

[Bridge]
The sun will rise, but something’s slipping through,
A darkness with its teeth, that’s waiting out of view.
We’ll laugh, we’ll love, but nothing stays the same,
The shadow’s creeping closer, calling out our names.
Oh, calling out our names...

[Outro]
In the early light, we’ll hold on tight,
But the shadow waits, just out of sight.
We’ll smile, we’ll plan, but we can’t outrun
The shadow before dawn, the shadow before dawn.

metadata.lyrics:
[Intro]

[Verse]
I watch you from across this empty room,
You’re miles away, but I'm so close to you.
My heart is heavy, tied down with doubt,
Wonderin’ if I'm worth it or if I’m wearing out.

[Pre-Chorus]
Used to be we’d laugh until we cried,
Now silence is the place we hide.
I reach out, but it slips away,
Fading like the light at the end of day.

[Chorus]
Where are we going, now that we’re here?
Lost in the space between hope and fear.
Once, we couldn’t stand a single inch apart,
Now I’m just someone you’re learning to guard.
Where are we going, and where did we start?

[Verse]
I miss the nights when nothing mattered more
Than being so close, breathing in each other’s warmth.
You were my reason, my steady ground,
But now I feel like I let you down.

[Pre-Chorus]
Maybe I’m wrong, maybe it’s me,
A shadow of what I used to be.
I know you blame me, you don’t have to say,
But I never thought it’d end this way.

[Chorus]
Where are we going, now that we’re here?
Caught in the echoes of love we can’t hear.
Used to be I’d find myself in your eyes,
Now I’m just lost in the silent goodbyes.
Where are we going, what did we leave behind?

[Bridge]
They say love fades, but I didn’t believe,
Thought we were different, thought we could see.
Now I’m just reaching for pieces of you,
Wonderin' if we can make it through.
Do you remember when you needed me close?
When every heartbeat was one we chose?
I’m still that person, buried deep,
But where are you when I try to speak?

[Chorus]
Where are we going, now that we’re here?
Wrapped in the shadows of all our fear.
We had it once, a fire so bright,
Now it’s just embers, swallowed by night.
Where are we going, will we ever find our way back?

[Outro]
I never wanted it to end like this,
Caught between broken promises and faded bliss.
I’ll hold on to the memory, the touch of your hand,
But I wonder, will we ever stand.
Together again, like we used to be?
Or are we just two souls, drifting out to sea?
Where are we going, now that we’re here,
Drowning in a love we can barely feel.
